data.title: Case Study 1
data.meta_description: CASE STUDY 1 - Free download as Word Doc (.doc / .docx), PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. The Victoria Memorial in Kolkata was constructed between 1906 and 1921 as a memorial to Queen Victoria. It was conceived by Lord Curzon and designed in a combination of classical European and Mughal architectural styles using white Makrana marble. The Victoria Memorial now serves as a prominent art museum and tourist destination maintained by the Ministry of Culture, housing artifacts from Victoria's life and 3,500 objects related to her memory.
